characteristics.name: Details
characteristics.$text:
An injured animal is often the most dangerous. Injured Jiralhanae will enter a berserk rampage when close to death in a last attempt to make one more kill.


If the active Jiralhanae unit has 2 or more wounds already, they can spend a Special Order result to add 1 to their Speed stat for a Sprint action made in activation.


This movement must be used to enter a cube with an enemy model. the Jiralhanae player may reroll 1 die during the resulting Fight test.

characteristics.name: Details
characteristics.$text:
If a friendly model begins their activation pinned, you may spend a Special Order result to perform a free Stand Up action first, then continue with the model's normal 2 short /1 long action.

Atriox personally may use special orders available to Jiralhanae and the Banished.


Atriox may be taken in place of 2 other Banished when drafting your Banished fireteam, if you are using the drafting rules from the Rulebook.

characteristics.name: Details
characteristics.$text:
If there is a friendly Banished model in the same cube or an adjacent cube to the active model at the start of its activation, then the active model is permitted to take the same short action twice during its activation.


Note this isn't allowing extra actions, it's just removing the usual obligation to use different action when taking tow short actions in the activation.

characteristics.name: Details
characteristics.$text: After an activation by either player, the Special Order command die result may be spent to remove the activation token from a friendly Sangheili Mercenary that is off the board (due to being killed but not yet respawned). This means the controlling player can and must take a turn to activate the model before the end fo the current round.
